Definition.WordDefinition: Urethra \U*re"thra\, n. [L., fr. Gr. ?. See {Urine}.] (Anat.) The canal by which the urine is conducted from the bladder and discharged. [1913 Webster]
urethra n : duct through which urine is discharged in most mammals and which serves as the male genital duct [also: {urethrae} (pl)]
